d=v\cdot t \;
\;v_M=\frac{2d}{t_M} \; and \;v_P=\frac{d}{t_P} 
\begin{align} & Mark's\; average\; speed: v_M \\ & Pat's\; average\; speed:v_P \\ & distance\; driven\; by Pat\; :d \\ & time\; taken\; by\; Mark:t_M \\ & time\; taken\; by\; Pat:t_P \\ & ratio\; of\; number\; of\; hours\; mark\; spends\; driving\; to\; the\; meeting\; to\; the\; number\; of\; hours\; \\  & pat\; spends\; driving\; to\; meeting\;=\frac{t_M}{t_P} \\ \end{align}
\begin{align}    \frac{2d}{t_M} & =\frac{4}{3} \cdot \frac{d}{t_P}  \\ \end{align}
\begin{align}    \frac{t_M}{t_P} & =\frac{3}{2}  \\ \end{align}
